RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 22000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ON THE MONEY RED stalked the early speed, took over when allowed three wide on the bend, angled in as he lengthened command under urging in the lane and maintained control while kept to task to the waning yards. HIGHLY PERFECT broke alertly, was rated from outside, moved to the inside with four furlongs left, picked up his pace on the turn, swung out three wide nearing the quarter pole, moved clear for second upper stretch, could only make up minor ground on the leader the last eighth but proved easily second best. ST. LOUIE LOUIE moved up quickly to contest the pace from inside, did not stay with ON THE MONEY RED on the bend, was no match for the pair in the stretch but was unchallenged for third. RUN THE TABLE displayed early speed just outside ST. LOUIE LOUIE and gave way the final quarter mile. GOVERNOR ATTACK dwelt at the break, was hustled along while staying well off the inside, proved unresponsive to urging at the head of the lane, was eased and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: St. Louie Louie
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, no match for top pair

ENTRY.NAME: Run the Table
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide speed, gave way last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Governor Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: dwelt start, stayed off rail, no response, eased late, walked off

ENTRY.NAME: On the Money Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, let out 3 wide turn, drive thru stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Highly Perfect
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, angled in 1/2, angled out 1/4, easily 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LASTFORTINOFAMILY advanced in hand two wide on the backstretch to gain the lead into the second bend, widened his lead when asked shortly after that, was under urging until inside the last sixteenth, proving much the best. CAMPAIGN SPY in contention early from inside, did not keep up two wide on the second turn, lodged his bid into the lane, moved to the rail upper stretch and caught ROAD GAME for second. ROAD GAME gradually progressed three wide to threaten on the second bend but slowly wore down inside the last eighth. FORT RIDGE moved up from outside to be a factor four wide on the backstretch and second turn but gave way for the drive. W W TRAFALGAR was hustled to a clear early lead but began to yield with three furlongs to go.

ENTRY.NAME: W W Trafalgar
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: used early inside

ENTRY.NAME: Campaign Spy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide 1/4, angled in stretch, got 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Lastfortinofamily
ENTRY.COMMENT: much the best, driving

ENTRY.NAME: Road Game
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Fort Ridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide, gave way last 1/4

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIVA VIOLENCE shared the early lead two wide while in hand, moved ahead when allowed on the bend, widened her lead under urging in the stretch and maintained control under steady handling. NOT TO BE DENIED hustled early, moved to the inside nearing the half mile marker, swung out four wide into the lane, drifted out midstretch, held a straight path the final eighth, closed well but came up short. MAZLAN progressed three wide to threaten with two furlongs to go but slowly wore down for the stretch run. ROARINGLIKETHUNDER displayed early speed from inside but gradually began to yield once on the turn. JEMEZ FALLS chased from outside, was two wide taking the bend, angled to the outside upper stretch and had little to offer. HUQOOQ soon trailed, was steadied briefly when her path was taken nearing the half mile marker, angled out, stayed well off the inside through the turn and was empty for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Roaringlikethunder
ENTRY.COMMENT: gradually yielded inside

ENTRY.NAME: Viva Violence
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide, clear, held

ENTRY.NAME: Huqooq
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Not to Be Denied
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in 1/2, 4 wide stretch bid, drifted out 1/8, closing

ENTRY.NAME: Mazlan
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide bid turn, weakened stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Jemez Falls
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide turn, angled outside stretch, empty

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ APPROVED rated on the front end from off the rail, was roused leaving the bend, began to wear down some in the late going but kept D' YANK at bay under steady handling. D' YANK raced in contention from inside, rallied along the rail in the lane, did not have enough in the waning yards but was easily second best. LATIN CASINO was checked behind TAP'S BIG SHOT leaving the chute, soon moved up between rivals to vie for the lead outside TIZ APPROVED, did not stay with that one on the turn and flattened out for the drive. TAP'S BIG SHOT lugged in some leaving the chute, stayed close from outside for a half mile but gave way the last two furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: D' Yank
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail bid, easily 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Approved
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated 2 wide, roused leaving turn, held

ENTRY.NAME: Latin Casino
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: checked leaving chute, 3 path turn, flattened out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Tap's Big Shot
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-path turn, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIFE OF SATURDAYS soon shared the early lead while in hand from inside, moved clear when allowed on the bend, floated out some entering the lane then gradually drifted out as she opened up on the field, continued to drift in the late going but maintained full control. SWEET JUSTICE forwardly placed between rivals, came five wide into the stretch and edged ahead for the place inside the last eighth. BEIRUT BEAUTY gradually angled out trying to gain a clear path leaving the chute, bumped with ABBMAR, made it to the outside before finishing a quarter mile, took over second from outside on the bend, swung out to path four into the lane, battled to hold her position but did not have enough left late. ABBMAR was pinched between horses shortly after leaving the chute, dropped back and moved toward the inside, progressed from outside on the turn and gradually lugged in as she rallied belatedly deep stretch. ASHLEY ELIZABETH angled in between horses nearing the half mile pole, was three wide leaving the bend, lacked a significant stretch bid, was steadied behind ABBMAR deep stretch and altered out. BOBBIE TOO TOO displayed early speed just outside LIFE OF SATURDAYS, found herself boxed in on the turn, steadily yielded in the lane and also lugged in deep stretch. PECOS AUTUMN broke well but soon retreated, moved to the inside nearing the bend, improved position some along the rail, was checked behind BOBBIE TOO TOO deep stretch and finished in hand. BAILESTON LASSIE angled in some leaving the chute and also bumped with ABBMAR, chased from outside and was never a factor. PRINCESS MANDII steadily yielded.

ENTRY.NAME: Life of Saturdays
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, let out turn, 2-path into stretch, gradually drifted out

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Mandii
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 path, steadily faded

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbie too Too
ENTRY.COMMENT: boxed in turn, lugged in late

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Justice
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly between, 3-5 path turn, got 2nd inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Beirut Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped early, 2-4 path turn, dueled for 2nd, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Abbmar
ENTRY.COMMENT: pinched early, 4 wide 1/4, lugged in late

ENTRY.NAME: Baileston Lassie
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped early, 3-5 path turn, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Ashley Elizabeth
ENTRY.OWNER: Indian Hills Farm (King) and Randazzo Jr Frank C
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide 1/4, steadied late, altered out

ENTRY.NAME: Pecos Autumn
ENTRY.OWNER: Bugnitz John Elsner Brad and Rule Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, checked late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 78. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since March 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO MADI GO broke a bit inward, brushing with CARSON RESERVE, was settled, moved to the inside with a half mile to go, began her rally on the bend, angled outside LICHITA upper stretch, took the advantage nearing the final sixteenth then drew off under hand urging. LICHITA was sent to gain the early lead then allowed to relax, came off the inside some entering the lane, roused upper stretch, began to wear down inside the last furlong but lasted for the place. THINK BLUE prominent just off the inside, angled out on the turn, came into the stretch from path five then could only pull away for third. DOROTA pressed the early speed from outside, floated out some into the stretch and gave way. CARSON RESERVE crowded briefly at the break, moved to the outside early on and showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Lichita
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent to lead,rated through turn,2-path into stretch,no match late

ENTRY.NAME: Think Blue
ENTRY.OWNER: Cappel Sue Hille Don Rosendohl Robert and Mullins Charles
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Carson Reserve
ENTRY.OWNER: Tinsley Austin and La Mew Diane
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Go Madi Go
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in 1/2,roused turn,angled out stretch,drew clear last 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Dorota
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 2-4 path turn, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce March 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIRLOLAMO'GLORY broke with the pack but was settled well back, was two wide on the bend, fanned out some entering the lane, rallied under urging and caught CRANKSHAFT in the final strides. CRANKSHAFT shared the lead from inside, moved clear when allowed on the turn, widened command under urging in the stretch, began to wear down the final sixteenth and was outfinished. PACHI vied for the lead from between horses, did not stay with CRANKSHAFT on the bend and gradually drifted out through the stretch. LONESOME DREAM disputed the pace from outside on the backstretch, failed to keep up on the turn, came widest into the lane and gradually angled out through the lane. DUST DANCER well placed between rivals early, faded from inside on the bend.

ENTRY.NAME: Crankshaft
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, weakened last 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Pachi
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2-4 path turn, gradually drifted out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Dust Dancer
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded inside turn

ENTRY.NAME: Lonesome Dream
ENTRY.OWNER: Bugnitz John Elsner Brad and Rule Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-5 path turn, weakened, gradually angled out

ENTRY.NAME: Girlolamo'glory
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled back, 2-3 path turn, got up in time
